radiographic_examinations.findings: Absence of an aortic knuckle on the left side of the mediastinum; right border of the descending thoracic aorta noted on the right side of the spine.

Right-sided aorta giving three branches: left common carotid, right common carotid, and right subclavian; left subclavian artery not visualized in the mediastinum; communicating with small-caliber left vertebral artery; right-sided tracheal bronchus noted; right main bronchus compressed; patchy area of consolidation in the medial basal segment of the right lower lobe.

Absence of flow-related enhancement in the left vertebral artery, likely due to flow reversal; flow enhancement noted in the left vertebral artery joining the left subclavian artery upon repeated TOF-MRA.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Flow enhancement was noted in the left vertebral artery upon repeating TOF-MRA.
